==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Symposium
<hw>Sym*po"si*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Symposia</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., fr. Gr.
<grk>sympo`sion</grk> a drinking party, feast; <grk>sy`n</grk> with +
<grk>po`sis</grk> a drinking. See <er>Syn-</er>, and cf.
<er>Potable</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A drinking together; a merry
feast.</def> <rj><au>T. Warton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A collection of short essays by different authors on
a common topic; -- so called from the appellation given to the
philosophical dialogue by the Greeks.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Symptom</ent>⟦br⟧
